task.summary: Default task
Added Square object with Test to verify surface area is calculated correctly
Added Rectangle object with Test to verify surface area is calculated correctly
Added Triangle object with Test to verify surface area is calculated correctly
Added Circle object with Test to verify surface area is calculated correctly
Created an Abstract Class so I can add Shapes to a general Shape list.
Add ShapeStack and init constructor that accepts new Shapes
ShapeStack has a empy constructor and a method for passing a new stackset.
Added a toString override so that each shape will display it's own type (S,R,T,C). Made sure there was an abstract method in the super class Shape.
Created the method stack which will iterate over the shapes in a stack. stack sorts elements by comparing each shapes area. Then the output is a string representation of the list.
Clean up sub-class shapes since making the superclass. Now they all have area and sides even though circle does not utilize sides.
Added documentation to make the constructor arguments more clear.
Mistyped "triangle" instead of "circle" in comments. @DocumentationError
Fixed issue with line break not occuring for Assert examples.
Added second Assert to verify getArea algorithm is set correctly and not made to pass one value.

Additional arguement validation neccessary for Isosceles triangle. It is mathmatically impossible for the hypotenuse of an right triangle to be shorter than the base or half the base of an isosceles triangle.
Added assertion to verify shapes can not be created with negative values.
Remove beforeTest setup since I only use it for one assertion.
Removed Asserts that never represent failed state
Modify Tests to specify tested object as "underTest" for readability.
Remove Hypotenuse check from Unit test. assertion can not test failure.
modify Shape assert tests to rename tests for clarity.
Modify Shapes to no longer accept zero length knowing full well that length .4 while still a positive length would round down to 0. I accept this as I am only working with whole number lengths.
Square extends Rectangle. Square Tests removed that are redundant with rectangle tests
Reverting Square Test changes. Tests for subclasses are commonly maintained incase of a new override in the furture.
Removed int[] sides from superClass shape. Assign specific values for supclass shapes. Length and width for rectangle and square. Base and hypotenuse for triangle. Diameter remains for circle.
Fixed issue with ShapeStacker pointing to passed List. Refactored assert names. Added Asserts for calling stack and toString on empty ShapeStacker.
Some additional thoughts
